        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Generating a barcode with a correct length length (for example, a 13-chars ean13 code) returns exception, saying \"\"1234567890123\" should have a length of 13 characters\". Even with a \"'withChecksum' => false\" in the Object options, the checksum is always appended, because of the \"_mandatoryChecksum\" default option in most of the adapters. I don't understand why this option is set, and I think I should be able to pass a complete ean13 with my own checksum. So, I just commented out the \"$this->_mandatoryChecksum = true;\" line in Zend_Barcode_Object_Ean13.php."
        },
