        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49395",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Even if I can understand your question, why can't you simply give it: substr($code, 0, 12) and it will append the checksum without problem?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T10:43:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T10:43:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49396",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just because I spend much time understanding why I couldn\u2019t pass a simple and complete ean13, and because this class should have an out-of-the-box functionning.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T10:52:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T10:52:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49397",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The out-of-the-box is to provide the text to encode (and only the text to encode) and Zend_Barcode will append (if nececessary but in case of EAN13 it's mandatory) the checksum for you.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T11:59:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T11:59:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49398",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, but can you tell me why is this param mandatory\u00a0? It seems that removing it does not break anything. Or is there a way to deactivate it without altering the class\u00a0?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T12:16:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T12:16:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49399",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Because it's in the standard (http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/European_Article_Number). You must have a checksum for an EAN13. It isn't the case for all barcodes. That's why we have 'withChecksum' option. But in case of EAN13, you have '_mandatoryChecksum' that overrides the value of the 'withChecksum' option. Because of the interaction with Zend_Validate_Barcode, we can't provide (today) a complete text with an incorporated checksum to the EAN13 object.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T12:25:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T12:25:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49400",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My question is: do you want a documentation with a more complete explanation on this point or the ability to provide the 13 characters?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T12:27:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T12:27:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49401",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In fact, any of the solutions would save time :) but maybe, the class could check if the checksum is provided by the barcode string, and remove it itself if necessary.\r\n\r\nI understand the blocking with Zend_Validate_Barcode, but if I just remove the _mandatoryChecksum param, the barcode validates successfully. What\u2019s wrong with this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gordontesos",
                        "name": "gordontesos",
                        "displayName": "Damien Nicolas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T12:43:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T12:43:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49402",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I can add a check to verify that the provided length is exactly the '_barcodeLength' and in this case not appending the checksum. But this won't be possible to provide a barcode of 5 characters + 1 checksum. Because I have also a '_addLeadingZeros' to complete a partial barcode. And I don't know how to determine if a text to encode is an error, a partial or a complete barcode.\r\n\r\nYou can of course remove '_mandatoryChecksum' in your copy of the library but I can't do this in ZF library. The problem will be for you for upgrading. The other solution is to extend Zend_Barcode_Object_Ean13 in your own library and to use the 'barcodeNamespace' option. In this case, the upgrade to ZF 1.12 won't be a problem :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-01-03T13:04:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-01-03T13:04:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49812",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "bq. but I can't do this in ZF library\r\n\r\nDoes this mean the issue can be closed as \"Wont' Fix\"?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-02-26T06:56:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-02-26T06:56:20.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
